            <originalsloc id="aspace_23cc55575806d4b530ca00513adf84f5">
               <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
               <p>The entire collection can be located in the Edmund T. Silk Papers (MS 1614).   The papers consist of the handwritten manuscript, the annotated typescript, and duplicating negative microfilm for Edmund Taite Silk's unpublished work, Exposicio Fratris Nicolai Trevethi Anglici Ordinis Predicatorum Super Boecio de Consolacione. Research materials and a small amount of personal and professional correspondence of Edmund and Eleanor Silk complete the collection.</p>
               <p>HM 281 only consists of : the use copy of: Edmund Taite Silk's unpublished work, Exposicio Fratris Nicolai Trevethi Anglici Ordinis Predicatorum Super Boecio de Consolacione.</p>
            </originalsloc>
